ot;&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;281&quot; frameborder=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;" style="width: 250px; height: 140px; background: url(https://i.ytimg.com/vi/_LnPKuejwNA/hqdefault.jpg) 50% 50% no-repeat; background-size: cover"></button></div>Another great piece of grotesque and surreal horror by A. V. Dossow, you are truly getting better with each game, this one actually got me scared for a hot second there.<p></p><p>The story is really good as usual and the fact that is pseudo grounded on things that COULD happen makes it more unnerving. The main character this time around was really likable which ended up making things...worse, specially with the abundance of choices we can make and the consequences...(I loved the multiple endings and choices!)</p><p>And that message after Game Over...it hurts.</p><p><br>Keep up the good work!<br></p></div><div class="post_footer"><a data-register_action="community_reply" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Faxelvejardossow.itch.io%2Fa-house-for-alesa&amp;intent=community" class="post_action reply_btn">Reply</a></div></div></div></div><div class="community_post_replies top_level_replies"><div id="post-8004825" class="community_post is_reply has_vote_column" data-post="{&quot;id&quot;:8004825,&quot;user_id&quot;:4762296}"><div class="post_grid"><div class="post_votes"><a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Faxelvejardossow.itch.io%2Fa-house-for-alesa&amp;intent=community" title="Vote up" class="vote_up_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_up" height="20" width="20" version="1.1" aria-hidden viewbox="0 0 24 24"><polygon points="2 18 12 6 22 18" /></svg></a> <a data-register_action="community_vote" href="https://itch.io/login?return_to=https%3A%2F%2Faxelvejardossow.itch.io%2Fa-house-for-alesa&amp;intent=community" title="Vote down" class="vote_down_btn vote_btn"><svg role="img" class="svgicon icon_vote_down" height="20" width="20"